# TV Info Panel — Repo Rules

## Product intent
- Keep this repo simple: one TV-friendly dashboard page with a few useful panels.
- Favor readability from across a room over dense information.
- Prefer boring server-side integrations for private data instead of TV-side auth.

## Local-first workflow
- Build and verify locally before discussing Ubuntu deployment.
- The default local URL is `http://localhost:3030`.
- Calendar should degrade cleanly to sample/fallback data when no private ICS URL is configured.

## Deployment guidance
- Suggested Ubuntu target path: `~/projects/tv-info-panel`
- Normal deploy flow: local edit -> push to GitHub -> pull on Ubuntu
- Keep runtime simple: `npm start` or `docker compose up -d`
- Fire TV should point to the hosted dashboard URL using a kiosk browser such as Fully Kiosk Browser

## Engineering guidance
- Avoid adding a heavyweight frontend framework unless the simple HTML/JS app becomes limiting.
- Keep secrets in `.env`, never in committed config files.
- Keep panel fetches server-side when tokens, cookies, or private feeds are involved.
